Reasoning: The paper discusses a novel approach to learning from complex demonstrations using a deep neural network, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the implementation of the proposed model for sensorimotor learning, which involves robotics (cs.RO). The use of a neural network to model the transfer of swing leg control from the brain to the spinal cord suggests the involvement of neuroscience (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the physiological basis of the proposed neural network architecture, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the use of the proposed model for image processing, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV).
